{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan an Nasai","section":{"21":{"eng-name":"The Book of Funerals","ara-name":"كتاب الجنائز"}},"section_detail":{"21":{"hadithnumber_first":1818,"hadithnumber_last":2089,"arabicnumber_first":1818,"arabicnumber_last":2089}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1818,"arabicnumber":1818,"text":"It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that the Messenger of Allah said:\"None of you should wish for death. Either he is a doer of good, so perhaps he may do more good, or he is an evildoer but perhaps he will give up his evil ways","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":21,"hadith":1},"chapter":{"id":1,"ara-name":"باب تَمَنِّي الْمَوْتِ ","eng-name":"Wishing For Death","isFirstHadith":true}}]}